## Design Context

### Users

- EquipQR serves multi-tenant fleet and equipment management teams, with primary emphasis on field technicians working on mobile devices in real job-site conditions.
- Secondary users include shop and operations staff on desktop, but core interaction decisions should prioritize technician speed and legibility first.
- The core job to be done is to complete equipment, work order, and status updates quickly and accurately with minimal friction, even under time pressure.

### Brand Personality

- Personality: professional, technical, and practical.
- Tone should communicate confidence, control, and reliability without looking flashy or playful.
- UI copy and visual treatment should feel operationally credible for enterprise maintenance and rental workflows.

### Aesthetic Direction

- Visual direction: clean enterprise, structured and data-forward.
- Use both light and dark mode as first-class experiences with equal polish.
- Use balanced brand accents with semantic status colors; avoid over-saturating large surfaces with brand color.
- Continue using existing EquipQR design tokens, shadcn/ui primitives, and Tailwind semantic classes as the default implementation path.

### Design Principles

- Optimize for speed and clarity in high-frequency technician workflows.
- Keep layouts systematic and predictable so users can scan and act quickly.
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility baseline across components and flows.
- Use subtle motion for feedback and orientation only, and respect reduced-motion preferences.
- Preserve consistency through shared component patterns, spacing, and semantic color usage.
